---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Third-Party Reproduction" description="Guide to third-party reproduction options including donor eggs, donor sperm, donor embryos, and gestational surrogacy with costs and legal considerations.">
	<section class="hero-mini">
		<div class="container">
			<nav class="breadcrumb">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<a href="/treatments/">Treatments</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<span>Third-Party Reproduction</span>
			</nav>
			<h1>Third-Party Reproduction</h1>
			<p>Building families with donor eggs, donor sperm, donor embryos, and gestational carriers.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="intro-box">
				<h2>Overview</h2>
				<p>Third-party reproduction involves using eggs, sperm, embryos, or a uterus from someone other than the intended parents. These options help individuals and couples who cannot conceive with their own gametes or carry a pregnancy.</p>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Donor Sperm</h2>

			<div class="option-card">
				<div class="option-header">
					<div class="option-icon">üî¨</div>
					<div class="option-title">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>Sperm from a donor used for insemination (IUI) or IVF.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="who-uses">
					<h4>Who Uses Donor Sperm</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Single women</div>
						<div class="use-item">Same-sex female couples</div>
						<div class="use-item">Severe male factor infertility</div>
						<div class="use-item">Genetic condition carriers</div>
						<div class="use-item">Azoospermia (no sperm)</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="donor-types">
					<h4>Types of Donors</h4>
					<div class="types-grid">
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Anonymous</h5>
							<p>Identity not disclosed; limited contact information available</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Open-ID</h5>
							<p>Identity available to child at age 18</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-card">
							<h5>Known</h5>
							<p>Friend or family member</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-steps">
					<h4>Process</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Select a sperm bank (California Cryobank, Seattle Sperm Bank, Fairfax, etc.)</li>
						<li>Review donor profiles (physical traits, education, health history)</li>
						<li>Purchase vials (ICI or IUI-ready)</li>
						<li>Ship to your clinic</li>
						<li>Use with IUI or IVF</li>
					</ol>
				</div>

				<div class="cost-section">
					<h4>Costs</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Donor sperm vial</span>
							<span class="price">$500-$1,200</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Extended profile/photos</span>
							<span class="price">$50-$200</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Shipping</span>
							<span class="price">$200-$400</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Storage at clinic</span>
							<span class="price">$200-$500/year</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Donor Eggs</h2>

			<div class="option-card featured">
				<div class="option-header">
					<div class="option-icon">ü•ö</div>
					<div class="option-title">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>Eggs from a donor, fertilized with partner or donor sperm, with resulting embryo transferred to the recipient.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="who-uses">
					<h4>Who Uses Donor Eggs</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Diminished ovarian reserve</div>
						<div class="use-item">Premature ovarian insufficiency</div>
						<div class="use-item">Repeated IVF failure</div>
						<div class="use-item">Advanced maternal age (>42)</div>
						<div class="use-item">Genetic conditions</div>
						<div class="use-item">Same-sex male couples</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="comparison-table">
					<h4>Fresh vs. Frozen Eggs</h4>
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Factor</th>
								<th>Fresh</th>
								<th>Frozen</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td>Cost</td>
								<td><span class="price-tag high">$25,000-$45,000</span></td>
								<td><span class="price-tag">$15,000-$25,000</span></td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Wait time</td>
								<td>2-6 months</td>
								<td><span class="highlight">Immediate</span></td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Eggs received</td>
								<td>All eggs (15-25)</td>
								<td>Set number (6-8)</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td>Success rates</td>
								<td><span class="rate good">55-65%</span></td>
								<td><span class="rate moderate">45-55%</span></td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>

				<div class="cost-breakdown">
					<h4>Fresh Cycle Cost Breakdown</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Agency fee</span>
							<span class="price">$5,000-$8,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Donor compensation</span>
							<span class="price">$6,000-$15,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Donor screening/testing</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$5,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Donor medications</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$6,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Legal fees</span>
							<span class="price">$1,500-$3,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">IVF cycle</span>
							<span class="price">$10,000-$15,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item total">
							<span class="name">Total</span>
							<span class="price">$28,000-$52,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="success-box">
					<h4>Success Rates</h4>
					<div class="success-stats">
						<div class="success-stat">
							<span class="value">50-65%</span>
							<span class="label">Live birth per transfer</span>
						</div>
						<div class="success-stat">
							<span class="value">80-90%</span>
							<span class="label">Cumulative over multiple transfers</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="note">Success rates do NOT depend on recipient's age - they're based on donor's age.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Donor Embryos</h2>

			<div class="option-card">
				<div class="option-header">
					<div class="option-icon">üß¨</div>
					<div class="option-title">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>Embryos donated by other couples who completed their families through IVF.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="who-uses">
					<h4>Who Uses Donor Embryos</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Need both donor egg and sperm</div>
						<div class="use-item">Seeking affordable option</div>
						<div class="use-item">Comfortable with embryo "adoption"</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-steps">
					<h4>Process</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Apply through embryo donation program or agency</li>
						<li>Match with donating family (often anonymous)</li>
						<li>Complete legal contracts</li>
						<li>Prepare uterus for transfer</li>
						<li>Frozen embryo transfer</li>
					</ol>
				</div>

				<div class="cost-section">
					<h4>Costs</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Program/matching fee</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$8,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Legal fees</span>
							<span class="price">$1,000-$2,500</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Embryo transfer</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$5,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item total">
							<span class="name">Total</span>
							<span class="price">$7,000-$15,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="success-rate-badge">
					<span class="label">Success Rate</span>
					<span class="value">30-50% per transfer</span>
					<span class="note">Varies based on embryo quality and donor age at creation</span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Gestational Surrogacy</h2>

			<div class="option-card major">
				<div class="option-header">
					<div class="option-icon">ü§∞</div>
					<div class="option-title">
						<h3>What It Is</h3>
						<p>A gestational carrier (GC) carries a pregnancy for intended parents. The embryo is created through IVF using eggs and sperm from intended parents and/or donors - the carrier has no genetic connection to the baby.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="who-uses">
					<h4>Who Uses Gestational Surrogacy</h4>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Women without a uterus</div>
						<div class="use-item">Uterine problems</div>
						<div class="use-item">Medical conditions making pregnancy dangerous</div>
						<div class="use-item">Same-sex male couples</div>
						<div class="use-item">Single men</div>
						<div class="use-item">Repeated implantation failure</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="surrogacy-types">
					<h4>Types of Surrogacy</h4>
					<div class="types-compare">
						<div class="type-box preferred">
							<div class="type-badge">Most Common</div>
							<h5>Gestational Surrogacy</h5>
							<p>GC has no genetic connection to baby. Embryo created via IVF.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="type-box">
							<h5>Traditional Surrogacy</h5>
							<p>GC uses her own eggs. Rare and more complex legally.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-steps">
					<h4>Process</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Work with a surrogacy agency or find independent GC</li>
						<li>Extensive screening of potential carrier</li>
						<li>Legal contracts (required)</li>
						<li>IVF cycle: create embryos with intended parents' or donor gametes</li>
						<li>Transfer embryo(s) to gestational carrier</li>
						<li>Pregnancy and birth</li>
						<li>Legal process for parental rights</li>
					</ol>
				</div>

				<div class="cost-breakdown major">
					<h4>Comprehensive Cost Breakdown</h4>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Agency fee</span>
							<span class="price">$15,000-$30,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">GC compensation</span>
							<span class="price">$30,000-$60,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">GC medical/psychological screening</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$6,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Legal fees (both parties)</span>
							<span class="price">$10,000-$20,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">IVF + embryo transfer</span>
							<span class="price">$15,000-$25,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">GC health insurance or premiums</span>
							<span class="price">$15,000-$35,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">GC expenses (maternity, travel)</span>
							<span class="price">$5,000-$15,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Escrow management</span>
							<span class="price">$1,000-$3,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item total">
							<span class="name">Total</span>
							<span class="price">$100,000-$200,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="callout-box warning">
					<div class="callout-icon">‚öñÔ∏è</div>
					<div class="callout-content">
						<h4>Legal Considerations</h4>
						<p>Surrogacy laws vary significantly by state. Some states are very surrogacy-friendly (California, Nevada, Connecticut); others have restrictions or bans. Work with a reproductive attorney experienced in your state's laws.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Emotional & Ethical Considerations</h2>

			<div class="considerations-grid">
				<div class="consideration-item">
					<span class="icon">üí≠</span>
					<p>Consider counseling before and during the process</p>
				</div>
				<div class="consideration-item">
					<span class="icon">üí¨</span>
					<p>Think about disclosure: will you tell your child about their origins?</p>
				</div>
				<div class="consideration-item">
					<span class="icon">ü§ù</span>
					<p>Consider future contact with donors or carriers</p>
				</div>
				<div class="consideration-item">
					<span class="icon">üìö</span>
					<p>Research shows children conceived with donors do well when raised in supportive families</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="callout-box info">
				<div class="callout-icon">‚ÑπÔ∏è</div>
				<div class="callout-content">
					<h4>Disclosure</h4>
					<p>Child development experts generally recommend age-appropriate disclosure to children about their donor conception. Resources like the Donor Sibling Registry can help families connect.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<nav class="nav-footer">
				<a href="/treatments/ivf/" class="nav-prev">
					<span class="nav-label">Previous</span>
					<span class="nav-title">‚Üê IVF</span>
				</a>
				<a href="/treatments/preservation/" class="nav-next">
					<span class="nav-label">Next</span>
					<span class="nav-title">Fertility Preservation ‚Üí</span>
				</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

